snippet: Lindsey Stirling, who popularized her dubstep violin in videos that got millions of views, is tough to classify as a musician.
abstract: New York Times critics Jon Caramanica and Zachary Woolfe discuss hip-hop violinist Lindsey Stirling, whose classical-meets-dance music has catapulted her to online popularity, and where she fits into music world.

byline.original: By JON CARAMANICA and ZACHARY WOOLFE

lead_paragraph: Lindsey Stirling, who popularized her dubstep violin in videos that got millions of views, is tough to classify as a musician.

headline.seo: Lindsey Stirling’s Music Combines Classical and Dance
headline.main: Defining an Online Phenomenon: Virtuoso or a Wedding Band Star?
headline.print_headline: Defining an Online Phenomenon: Virtuoso or a Wedding Band Star?
